Uzbek teacher
Responsibilities:


to promote the formation of competent communication and writing in the Uzbek language;

helping students to master the educational program, motivating children;

conduct training sessions in primary and secondary schools;

professional approach to primary and secondary school students;

plan and implement the learning process;

evaluate the effectiveness and learning outcomes of students;


Requirements:


Higher pedagogical education (Master's degree is welcome);

Competent speech in Uzbek without accents, fluent Russian, English will be a great advantage;

Work experience of at least 2-3 years;


Terms:


Full-time working hours from 8 to 16:30 (weekly 22 academic hours), 5/7

